âœ¨ Q27: Remove Element âœ¨
ğŸ“Œ (Hinglish + Short + Coding Style)

ğŸ§® Given: Ek integer array nums hai aur ek value val di hui hai.

ğŸ› ï¸ Task:
Array me jitni bhi val value ke occurrences hai, sabko remove karo (in-place) ğŸ‘‡
â¡ï¸ Order change ho sakta hai, koi problem nahi.
â¡ï¸ Bas un elements ko rakhna hai jo val ke equal nahi hai.

ğŸ¯ Output:
Array me jitne elements val ke equal nahi hai, unka count k return karo.

ğŸ’¡ Simple Samajh:
Array me se val hatao, aur bache huye elements kitne hain woh k batao. ğŸ˜„
ğŸ‘‰ First k elements hi valid honge, baaki ignore.

ğŸ”¥ Example:
nums = [3,2,2,3], val = 3
Remove 3 â†’ [2,2,_ , _] â†’ k = 2

ğŸ‘¨â€ğŸ’» Ready to Code? ğŸš€

import java.util.*;
public class Coding {
    public static void main(String[] args) { 
        int arr[] = {1,2,3,3,4,4,4}; // ğŸ“Œ Array jisme hume target remove karna hai
        int target = 4;             // ğŸ¯ Jis element ko hatana hai (val)
        int k = 0; // ğŸ§® Yeh count karega ki kitne elements target ke alawa bache
        for(int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {  // ğŸ” Poore array ko check karo
            if(arr[i] != target) {             // ğŸ’¡ Agar element target ke equal nahi hai
                arr[k] = arr[i];               // ğŸ“ Toh usko array ke start me store karo
                k++;                            // â• Valid (non-target) elements ki counting badhao
            }
        }
        // ğŸ–¨ï¸ Sirf pehle k elements print karo, wahi valid (target removed) array hai
        for(int i = 0; i < k; i++) {
            System.out.print(arr[i] + " ");    // ğŸ“¤ Output without target: 1 2 3 3
        }
    }
}
